üí¶ VICIOUS CYCLES LAUNDRETTE LAUNCH ANNOUNCEMENT üí¶

An exhibition about a brain stuck on spin cycle.

Vicious Cycles Laundrette is the new solo show from Melbourne artist Ellen Porteus. For five days only, a Collingwood warehouse will be transformed into a larger-than-life art show. Inspired by a period of deep reflection and introspection, Vicious Cycles Laundrette confronts repeated behaviours, thoughts and habits that turn destructive. 
The collection of work spans the mediums of animation, print, sculpture and painting, in Porteus‚Äô signature colourful, bold and tongue-in-cheek style. This exhibition builds on Porteus‚Äô body of work exploring honesty, self obsession and personal development. ‚Äî

I fly home today after 5 weeks in New York. I decided to stay a while in the US because I had fallen into a big dumb rut in Melbourne, and whenever that happens I like to pull the rug out from under my feet and get uncomfortable.

It‚Äôs been a really important time for me, filled with both long periods of solitude and self reflection, and long periods of socialising, meetings and inspiration with incredible people. 
It‚Äôs been a long long 5 weeks, and I miss my amazing partner and my dog and my little slice of Melbourne so so much. I should feel exhausted but I don‚Äôt, I feel super excited and energised for what‚Äôs ahead. 
Here‚Äôs some pics of me getting outta that rut and looking 100% stoked.
